                        "content": "The nurse is teaching a client with hyperthyroidism about the prescribed medication, propylthiouracil. The nurse determines that teaching has been successful if the client states to report which symptom to the primary health care provider (PHCP)?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nAn adverse effect of propylthiouracil is agranulocytosis. The client needs to be alert for this adverse effect by noting the presence of fever or sore throat, which would be reported to the PHCP immediately. Excitability is not a side or adverse effect of this medication. Fatigue may be an occasional side effect of the medication but does not warrant PHCP notification.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, client understanding about the effects of propylthiouracil. Eliminate excitability and nervousness because they are comparable or alike. Regarding the remaining options, recalling that agranulocytosis is an adverse effect will direct you to the correct one.",
