                        "content": "The nurse provides education to the client with hyperthyroidism about potassium iodide before medication administration. The client is scheduled for a subtotal thyroidectomy. Which response by the client indicates understanding?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPotassium iodide is administered to hyperthyroid individuals in preparation for thyroidectomy to suppress thyroid function. Initial effects develop within 24 hours. Peak effects develop in 10 to 15 days. In most cases, plasma levels of thyroid hormone are reduced with propylthiouracil before potassium iodide therapy is initiated. Then potassium iodide, along with propylthiouracil, is administered for the last 10 days before surgery. Therefore, the remaining options are incorrect.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the therapeutic effect of potassium iodide. Eliminate options 1 and 3 first because they are comparable or alike. From the remaining choices, note the relationship between the diagnosis of hyperthyroidism and the correct option.",
                        "id": "edd0571b468645b0bfca85ca65d2a876",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b282c6fb0fed488c8143b62f26f6b657",
                                "content": "Administer methimazole with food."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "b50fc2a12ac540429a3d16649be5f68b",
                                "content": "Place the client on a low-calorie, low-protein diet."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "33444aef2b4e4262bf084c98cde659ac",
                                "content": "Assess the client for unexplained bruising or bleeding."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "bdb73988680f4088ac7bf98c1f6107ca",
                                "content": "Instruct the client to report side and adverse effects such as sore throat, fever, or headaches."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "18cdb3eac83041a9ae4aaa5cf0fe8e62",
                                "content": "Use special radioactive precautions when handling the client's urine for the first 24 hours following initial administration."
                            }
                        ],
